:Class APLGuiParms
    ⎕IO←0 ⋄ ⎕ML←3

    ∇ r←CreateDefaults
      :Access Public Shared
    ⍝ This generates a parameter space with default settings to be used as "global parameters".
    ⍝ * `caption`<br />Used by all forms automatically.
    ⍝ * `honorCaptionForSizeCalc`<br />Takes the full caption into account when calculating the size of a form.
    ⍝ * `honorStatusbarForSizeCalc`<br />Take the status bar (incl. a progress bar) into account when calculating the size of a form.
    ⍝ * `icon`<br />Might become an Icon used by all forms.
    ⍝ * `fontStandard`<br />Font used for forms. That's what controls will inherit.
    ⍝ * `fontInput`<br />Font used for input fields, tables and lists.
    ⍝ * `fontLables`<br />Font used for Lables.
    ⍝ * `parmType`<br />Carries the name (type) of the parameter namespace.
    ⍝ * `sysMenu`<br />Shall any form have a system menu?
    ⍝ * `centerin`<br />If this becomes a ref to a form then all objects will center within that form automatically..
    ⍝ * `maxButton`<br />Shall the GUI have a max button?
    ⍝ * `minButton`<br />Shall the GUI have a min button?
    ⍝ * `regKey`<br />Used to save Posn & Size in the Windows Registry. Refer to help for details.
    ⍝ * `testMode`<br />Set this to 1 only if you are running test cases of some sort. Refer to the help for details.
    ⍝ * `timeout`<br />How long shall a dialog wait until the default button is pressed automatically (by a timer).
      r←##.APLGuiParameterSpace.Create
      r.caption←''
      r.honorCaptionForSizeCalc←1
      r.honorStatusbarForSizeCalc←1
      r.icon←''
      r.(fontStandard fontInput fontLables fontAPL)←CreateStandardFonts ⍬
      r.parmType←'APLGuiParms'
      r.sysMenu←1
      r.centerIn←⍬
      r.maxButton←1
      r.minButton←1
      r.regKey←''
      r.testMode←0
      r.timeout←0
     ⍝Done
    ∇

    ∇ r←CreateStandardFonts dummy;apl;label;input;standard
    ⍝ Creates 4 fonts to be used as standard, input, label and APL font.
      :Access Public Shared
      standard←(⎕NEW'Font'(('PName' 'Tahoma')('Size' 18)))
      input←(⎕NEW'Font'(('PName' 'Courier New')('Size' 18)))
      label←(⎕NEW'Font'(('PName' 'Tahoma')('Size' 15)))
      apl←(⎕NEW'Font'(('PName' 'APL385 Unicode')('Size' 19)))
      r←(standard input label apl)
    ∇

:EndClass
